    <p>
        <b>
            <a href="#close" class="hide">
                [x] click to close
            </a>
        </b>
    </p>
    <div id="map_vothC39" style="width: 250px; height: 250px;"></div>
                        <p class="placename">
                Gross-Rosen
            </p>
                            <p class="subcamp_of">
                <strong>Subcamp of: </strong>
                Gross-Rosen
            </p>
                            <p class="municipality">
                <strong>Location:</strong>
                Rogoźnica, Poland<br />
                            </p>
                            <div>
                Established in Silesia in 1940 as a satellite camp to Sachsenhausen, it became an independent camp in 1941. Work centered on a huge stone quarry and many sub-camps were established (reaching 60 in 1944).
            </div>
